The abrupt increase in deciduous Quercus and the marked rises in Ulmus, Fraxinus excelsior-t., Betula and Corylus pollen percentages indicate that the rapid spread of mixed deciduous forests at the expense of steppic vegetation and pine woods continued during VER-2 (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
